id": "call_H31YD4Q18xPlaXdBiEF1z5sL"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_K18dabyLfHMAtRad2xOd31Sl", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/django-10914\"}", "name": "board_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/benchmark/mas_centralize/django__django-10914/repeat_1/project_board/django-10914", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_K18dabyLfHMAtRad2xOd31Sl"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_zFbNCoHTG6ZhOVwZ7WZiUrLg", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/django-10914/000_issue.md\",\"content\":\"Title: Set default FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSION to 0o644\\n\\nRepository: django/django\\nBase commit: e7fd69d051eaa67cb17f172a39b57253e9cb831a\\n\\nProblem:\\nThe repository tests fail because the default value for FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS should be changed to 0o644. A failing test is test_override_file_upload_permissions in test_utils.tests.OverrideSettingsTests. The goal is to update the default, update documentation references and release notes, and adjust tests as minimally as possible.\\n\\nScope:\\n- Change default FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS to 0o644 (int) where it is defined.\\n- Add a Breaking change note to releases/3.0.txt (this target is 3.0 per discussion), mentioning old behavior and how to restore it by setting to None.\\n- Update docs references where the default or behavior is described (settings and deployment checklist).\\n- Adjust tests that rely on previous defaults.\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- Minimal code changes to implementation.\\n- Ensure tests pass in the test suite focused on utils tests.\\n\\nFiles of interest:\\n- django/core/files/storages.py and storage settings\\n- docs/topics/files/index.rst and settings docs\\n- releases/3.0.txt\\n\\nPlan:\\n1. Create tickets for Diagnose, Change default, Update docs, Add release note, Adjust tests, and QA.\\n2. Assign implementation ticket to Engineer.\\n3. After Engineer implements, send to CodeReviewer and QA.\\n\\nDeliverables:\\n- Patch changing default behavior and test updates.\\n- Project board tickets.\\n- Final summary once QA verifies the change.\\n\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/benchmark/mas_centralize/django__django-10914/repeat_1/project_board/django-10914/000_issue.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_zFbNCoHTG6ZhOVwZ7WZiUrLg"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_7k8Cpa7u775koe8YjRv63a2e", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/django-10914/001_diagnose.md\",\"content\":\"Title: Diagnose failing test_override_file_upload_permissions\\n\\nGoal:\\nReproduce and confirm failure cause for test_override_file_upload_permissions. Verify where FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS default is defined and how tests expect it.\\n\\nTasks:\\n- Run the failing test locally (or read tests) to see expected vs actual.\\n- Locate FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS default in settings module (django/conf/global_settings.py).\\n- Search codebase for references to FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS and FILE_UPLOAD_DIRECTORY_PERMISSIONS.\\n- Identify tests that assert default values and need updating.\\n\\nAcceptance:\\n- Clear description of where to change the default and list of tests to update.\\n\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/benchmark/mas_centralize/django__django-10914/repeat_1/project_board/django-10914/001_diagnose.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_7k8Cpa7u775koe8YjRv63a2e"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_aggj3DsAIt7HtJjIF2f3xmvS", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/django-10914/002_change_default.md\",\"content\":\"Title: Implementation: Change FILE_UPLOAD_PERMISSIONS default to 0o644\\n\\nGoal:\\nSet FILE_UPLOAD_